        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> I see how many of you feel. I thank you for your realistic views on how I write. I will let you know, that I am an amature writer. I will make mistakes. I have a story to tell. It is my project, my goal to finish this story for your entertainment. That is why I put it through the "death test." If it doesnt withstand all of these dark burning flames, then it wont ever go far. I also want to see how I can evolve my thinking with this project of mine. Its not just a project, its also an experiment on ME. I can be anything I want, but I might not be good at what I can be. That is why "experiment" on my mind. Dont take me wrong, its an "intellect test" on how I use my literary skills as well as other english structures. I, like many of you, have many goals and dreams that I want to fufill. The difference is that I will go through hell for my dreams. I accomplished a few so far and it nearly ended my first career. I was so into my goal that I began to tell the "experts" at these huge industrial corporations about what they do wrong and why they think they are correct. I still stand with my views and a few of these scientests and specialists of 20+ years now understand what I told them. If you want to see just how smart I am, you can compare me if you search for the following on the internet search enginges. "THE RADIOACTIVE BOYSCOUT"  This guy was my friend in the Navy and we used to talk about many things that you would find intersting. Once again I would like to thank you for your critisism on my writing. I will continue to write till I believe that I can do no better. I hope that you all understand my point of view.</P><P>always thinking...(proccessing)...<BR>Velous</P><P>"I don't talk to dead people; I make them scream."</P><P>"I make dead people."</font></td>
