 nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'>Saminga</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> Needs mucho tightening, and your more active scenes need punch. Try cutting out a bunch of supercilious (Oh, Cazic-Thule, it still feels too early  in the morning for a word like that, or even thinking it.) *ahem* extra words in your sentences. Don't be too descriptive. If someone described everything that you were wearing, or everything in a modern day room, I would fall asleep. So, you have to balance enough description with not too much, and action scenes, which I personally hate, require some very fine tweaking. My necromancer story is mostly a monologue, but I still like it. My rogue piece is mostly dialogue, my SK piece is mostly philosophical/emotive in nature, my paladin piece has a few choice bits of action which I'm still tweaking, and my monk is hard to explain, but isn't active at all, but more thoughtful. My bard piece reads like a humour piece :P</P><P>Anyway, if you are willing to wait on my lazy butt editing, you can mail me your manuscript at <a href="mailto:cailean@whoever.com">cailean@whoever.com</a></P><P>If you'd like to see anything of mine to kinda learn from, and I'm still learning myself, check out this search:</P><P><a href="http://www.google.com/search?hl=en&ie=UTF-8&oe=UTF-8&q=%22Cailean+Darkwater%22&btnG=Google+Search" target="_blank">http://www.google.com/search?hl=en&ie=UTF-8&oe=UTF-8&q=%22Cailean+Darkwater%22&btnG=Google+Search</a></P><P>Constructive criticism is welcome, flames are not :)</P><P>As to being an amateur, don't flame this poor fellow too much, all people can start out needing work, and we should encourage them. It's kinda like watching a noob necro mess up fearkiting or something. You don't yell abuse at them and laugh at them, you say "No, you doing it wrong, try this maybe?" Let's offer some constructive advice instead of flaming. He hasn't done anything WRONG, or silly, just asking us, his peers, for advice with something. And it sure as hell isn't a vanity post.</P><P>Saminga Amaranth, speaking as Cailean Darkwater, 60th Bad Girl and vaguely successful writer, Avatars of Discord, Rodcet Nife.</P><P>Good girls go to Heaven, bad girls FD and /q out.</font></td>
